Our project involved addressing a technological uncertainty related to the effect of importing a project plan in CSV format into our project work tracking application. We identified that our existing system had limited functionality for importing project plans, and we were uncertain about the compatibility of the CSV file format and structure with our application.

Overall, our R&D efforts focused on addressing the technological uncertainties related to importing project plans in CSV format, through systematic experimentation, prototyping, and innovation. The resulting custom software module and enhanced application functionality represent a significant innovation and a new solution to the technological challenges faced by our organization Overall, our R&D efforts focused on addressing the technological uncertainties

existing system had limited functionality for importing project plans, and we were uncertain about the compatibility of the CSV file format and structure with our application.

To address this uncertainty, we undertook significant experimentation, prototyping, and innovation efforts. We formulated a hypothesis about the compatibility of different CSV file formats and structures with our application, and tested this hypothesis through systematic experimentation. Through this process, we developed a custom CSV import module that seamlessly integrated with our project work tracking application.

Our R&D efforts focused on developing a new and novel solution to the technological uncertainty, which could not be resolved using standard practice or existing knowledge. By developing a custom software module and implementing enhanced functionality for manipulating and analyzing the data within our application, we were able to significantly improve our project management processes.
